computeTradeToMoveMarket(uint256,uint256.details: Note that this method uses the Babylonian square root method which has a small margin of error which will result in a small over or under estimation on the size of the trade needed.

params.reserveA: number of token A in the pair reserves
params.reserveB: number of token B in the pair reserves
params.truePriceTokenA: the nominator of the true price.
params.truePriceTokenB: the denominatornominator of the true price.

swapToPrice(address,address,address,addr.details: True price is expressed in the ratio of token A to token B.The caller must approve this contract to spend whichever token is intended to be swapped.

params.maxSpendTokenA: maximum to spend in tokenB. Note can be set to zero, thereby limiting the direction of trade.
params.to: deadline to limit when the trade can execute. If the tx is mined after this timestamp then revert.
params.tokenA: address of the second token in the uniswap pair.
params.truePriceTokenA: the nominator of the true price.
params.truePriceTokenB: the denominatornominator of the true price.
params.uniswapFactory: address of the uniswap factory used to fetch current pair reserves.
params.uniswapRouter: address of the uniswap router used to facilate trades.

computeTradeToMoveMarket(uint256,uint256.notice: Given the "true" price a token (represented by truePriceTokenA/truePriceTokenB) and the reservers in the uniswap pair, calculate: a) the direction of trade (aToB) and b) the amount needed to trade (amountIn) to move the pool price to be equalto the true price.

swapToPrice(address,address,address,addr.notice: Swaps an amount of either token such that the trade results in the uniswap pair's price being as close as possible to the truePrice.

userdoc.notice: Trading contract used to arb uniswap pairs to a desired "true" price. Intended use is to arb UMA perpetual synthetics that trade off peg. This implementation can ber used in conjunction with a DSProxy contract to atomically swap and move a uniswap market.
